Problem:-
You have a room behind a door and there are three bulbs inside the room. 
You can find its three switches outside the door.
You can switch them on and off as many times as you wish but once you open the door you cannot change them. 
Identify which switch is connected to which bulb.

Solution:-
Let the lightbulbs be X, Y and Z.
Switch on and off X for 5 to 10 times. 
Now immediately switch off X and switch on Y and open the door. 
The lightbulb which is on is Y. The lightbulb which is hot but off is X.
The lightbulb which is off and cold is Z.
